HEADWORD: Shintiism
<hw>Shin"ti*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chin. <ets>shin</ets> god + <ets>tao</ets>
way, doctrine.]</ety> <def>One of the two great systems of religious
belief in Japan. Its essence is ancestor worship, and sacrifice to dead
heroes.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Sintu</asp>, and
<asp>Sintuism</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
